  "title": "Site Architect, MRT Project",
  "description": "<ul><li>Architectural management/coordination for both Design & Site functions for a major MRT/LTA project</li><li>Manage the entire project processes including authority submission, drawing submission schedules based on the planned work progress</li><li>Coordinate and review all design matters with LTA, authorities, consultants, subcontractors, etc.</li><li>Liaise and communicate closely with client’s reps, consultants & contractors.</li><li>Produce architectural drawings as directed and as required for project, in an effective & professional manner.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree in Architecture from an accredited institution</li><li>Minimum 3-5 years of experience, with prior/present experience in MRT/LTA projects</li><li>Able to work under pressure in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Comfortable to work on a 5.5 days workweek</li></ul><p>If this opportunity aligns with your skills and experience, please submit your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong><br /><br />Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367<br />www.bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
